# Stakr - New Features & Components Rules

## CRITICAL NEW FEATURE REQUIREMENTS

- **CRITICAL**: All new features must include unit tests before implementation
- **CRITICAL**: All new components must be mobile-first and responsive
- **CRITICAL**: All new API endpoints must include authentication and authorization
- **CRITICAL**: All new features must follow Stakr's fairness principles
- **CRITICAL**: All new components must include proper accessibility attributes
- **CRITICAL**: All new features must include proper error handling
- **CRITICAL**: All new database operations must use parameterized queries
- **CRITICAL**: All new file uploads must include validation and security checks
- **CRITICAL**: All new user inputs must be validated and sanitized
- **CRITICAL**: All new features must include proper loading states
- **CRITICAL**: All new features must include proper empty states
- **CRITICAL**: All new features must be tested on mobile devices
- **CRITICAL**: All new features must include proper TypeScript types
- **CRITICAL**: All new features must follow existing naming conventions
- **CRITICAL**: All new features must include proper logging
- **CRITICAL**: All new features must be documented
- **CRITICAL**: All new features must include proper error boundaries
- **CRITICAL**: All new features must be optimized for performance
- **CRITICAL**: All new features must include proper state management
- **CRITICAL**: All new features must be accessible (WCAG 2.1 AA)

